column2: "Bravo, bravo I say. You've completely outwitted me, comrade."
"I was convinced you would be entirely without aid here... But it would seem you're far more adored than I ever imagined."
"But your fans aren't limited to the denizens of this fictitious world. You're even rubbing elbows with the Dark Falz."
"Where's Harriet?"
"Return Harriet."
"Harriet? Heheh, what do you mean? She's right in front of you."
"This black cocoon is Harriet...?"
"That is the [Profound Darkness]'s vessel. Something that exists at all points in history. This world is no different, you see."

"No matter how lofty a goal they strive for, no matter how beloved a figure they become,
they're destined to bring about the end of the world."

"The role of sacrifice has been recorded as
Harriet's. It was her unavoidable fate, if you will."
"...Don't you see, comrade? It's futile to try and save her. The best you can offer her is death."
"Isn't that your forte, after all? The very reason we are comrades? Hahahah!"
"I WILL save her."
"Are you done talking?"
"It's always save her and save him with you, do you even know what that word means? You couldn't save anyone!"
"Always choosing to sacrifice others in order to survive! In the past, in the present... And it will happen again!"
"I'll tear it all down! In this very spot! Everything will return to zero!"
"You... and [Persona], isn't this what you wanted?!"
"You don't know [Persona]."
"You're not [Persona]."
"...Silence, comrade! I am... I am more Dark Falz than anyone!"
"Born of the beginning, persisting into the future, record of the Guardian! I will rewrite you!"
